Start-
      Highest priority of styling-Inline style (inside an HTML element)
                                  External and internal style sheets (in the head section)
                                  Browser default or External CSS
      In CSS to Style-
      div.first {  } as we write.(<div class="fiirst">This div is 300px wide.</div>)
      p.dotted {  }(<p class="dotted">A dotted outline</p>)

     properties can have the following values:
                                   length - specifies a padding in px, pt, cm, etc.
                                   % - specifies a property(like-padding) in % of the width of the containing element
                                   inherit - specifies that the property should be inherited from the parent element


Home---------

IntroDuction-    Intro, Multiple Style sheets, use.

Syntax

Selectors-       Types(Simple,Combinator,Pseudo-class,Pseudo-elements,Attribute), Selector(element,id(#),class(.),Universal(*),Grouping(h1, h2, p{}).

How To Add CSS-  ways(External CSS,Internal CSS,Inline CSS), Multiple Style Sheets.

Comments-        Type(single-line,multi-line)(/* Set */).

Colors-          Color- Names, Background Color, Text Color, Border Color, Color Values.
                 RGB-   RGB Value-rgb(red, green, blue),rgba(red, green, blue, alpha), alpha value(0-1).
                 HEX -  HEX Value-#rrggbb(Black color-#000000,white color-#ffffff),#rgb(pink-#f0f).
                 HSL-   HSL Value-hsl(hue, saturation, lightness)example-hsl(0, 100%, 50%), hsla(hue, saturation, lightness, alpha), alpha(0.0-1.0).

Backgrounds-     color=
                 background-color,background-image,background-repeat,background-attachment,background-position,background, Opacity(Transparency), Transparency using RGBA
                 
                 Image=
                 In body, In elements.
                 
                 Repeat=
                 If the image above is repeated only horizontally(background-repeat: repeat-x;).
                 To repeat an image vertically, set(background-repeat: repeat-y;).
                 no repeatation, set(background-repeat: no-repeat;).
                 CSS background-position, set(background-position: right top;)

                 Background Attachment =
                 specifies whether the background image should scroll or be fixed.
                  background-attachment: fixed;     background-attachment: scroll;

                 Background Shorthand=
                 To specify all the background properties in one single property.
                 background: #ffffff url("img_tree.png") no-repeat right top;      
                 shorthand property the order of the property value(background-color,background-image,background-repeat,background-attachment,background-position));

Borders-
         allow you to specify the style, width, and color of an element's border.
         different border styles:
                         p.dotted {border-style: dotted;}
                         p.dashed {border-style: dashed;}
                         p.solid {border-style: solid;}
                         p.double {border-style: double;}
                         p.groove {border-style: groove;}
                         p.ridge {border-style: ridge;}
                         p.inset {border-style: inset;}
                         p.outset {border-style: outset;}
                         p.none {border-style: none;}
                         p.hidden {border-style: hidden;}
                         p.mix {border-style: dotted dashed solid double;}

           Border Width =
                          specifies the width of the four borders(border-width:5px;),(border-width: 5px 20px;),(border-width: 25px 10px 4px 35px;).

           Border Color =
                          used to set the color of the four borders(border-color: red;),(border-color: red green blue yellow;)
                                                    (border-color: transparent;)

           Border Sides =
                          specifying each of the borders (top, right, bottom, and left):
                                         (border-top-style: dotted;),(border-right-style: solid;),(border-bottom-style: dotted;),(border-left-style: solid;)

           Border Shorthand =
                              (border: 5px solid red;),(border-left: 6px solid red;),(border-bottom: 6px solid red;).

           Rounded Borders =
                             (border-radius: 5px;)

Margins-
          Margin = 
          used to create space around elements, outside of any defined borders(Negative values are allowed).
                  (margin-top: 100px;),(margin-bottom: 100px;),(margin-right: 150px;),(margin-left: 80px;)

          shorthand Property =
                    (margin: 25px 50px 75px 100px;)
           auto -- to horizontally center the element within its container(margin: auto;).
           Inherit--margin of the element(<p class="ex1">) be inherited from the parent element (<div>):
                            div {
                                   border: 1px solid red;
                                     margin-left: 100px;
                                }
                            p.ex{
                                  margin-left: inherit;
                                 }

                          <body>
                                <div>
                                    <p class="ex1">This paragraph has an inherited left margin (from the div element).</p>
                                </div>
                           </body>

            Margin Collapse =
            Top and bottom margins of elements are sometimes collapsed into a single margin that is equal to the largest of the two margins.
            This does not happen on left and right margins! Only top and bottom margins!

Padding-
         used to create space around an element's content, inside of any defined borders.
         Padding for Individual Sides--
                                     padding-top, padding-right, padding-bottom, padding-left.
         Padding Shorthand Property-(padding: 25px 50px 75px 100px;)
         Padding and Element Width- if an element has a specified width, the padding added to that element will be added to the total width of the element.
                              no matter the amount of padding, you can use the box-sizing property. This causes the element to maintain its actual width; if you increase the padding, the available content space will decrease.
                                    (box-sizing: border-box;)

Height, Width-
               height and width Values- auto, length, %, initial, inherit.
               Examples.
               Setting max-width


Box Model-
           used when talking about design and layout.
           It consists of: content, padding, borders and margins.
              div {
                   width: 300px;
                   border: 15px solid green;
                   padding: 50px;
                   margin: 20px;
                  }
              Width and Height of an Element.

Outline-
          Outline =
          a line drawn outside the element's border.
          outline properties: outline-style, outline-color, outline-width, outline-offset, outline.
          CSS Outline Style: dotted, dashed, solid, double, groove, ridge, inset, outset, none, hidden.

          Outline Width =
          specifies the width of the outline.
          values[thin (typically 1px), medium (typically 3px), thick (typically 5px), A specific size (in px,pt,cm,em,etc)]          

          Outline Color =
          used to set the color of the outline (outline-color: red;).

          Outline Shorthand =
           for setting the following individual outline properties: outline-width, outline-style (required), outline-color.
                       (outline: 5px solid yellow;)

          Outline Offset =
          adds space between an outline and the edge/border of an element (outline-offset: 15px;).

Text-
        Text Color =
        used to set the color of the text (color: blue;).
        Background Color (background-color: blue;).

        Text Alignment =
        (center,left,right,justify) 
        properties: 
                 text-align(text-align: center;)
                 text-align-last (use to align last word of element)
                 direction (use to change the direction of an element)
                 unicode-bidi(used to change the text direction of an element)
                 vertical-align- sets the vertical alignment of an element (baseline, text-top, text-bottom, sub, super)

         Text Decoration =
          properties: text-decoration-line, text-decoration-color, text-decoration-style, text-decoration-thickness, text-decoration.
          Add a Decoration Line to Text: overline, line-through, underline, overline underline.
          Specify a Color for the Decoration Line: (used to set the color of the decoration line) 
                      (text-decoration-line: overline underline;
                       text-decoration-color: purple;)
          Style for the Decoration Line: 
                               (text-decoration-line: underline;
                                text-decoration-style: double;)          
          Thickness for the Decoration Line: (text-decoration-thickness: 5px;)
          Shorthand Property: text-decoration-line (required)
                              text-decoration-color (optional)
                              text-decoration-style (optional)
                              text-decoration-thickness (optional)
           Small Tip: (text-decoration: none;)-- is used to remove the underline from links

           Text Transformation =
            used to specify uppercase and lowercase letters in a text or capitalize the first letter of each word.
            uppercase, lowercase, capitalize(text-transform: uppercase;)

            Text Spacing =
            properties: text: indent, letter-spacing, line-height, word-spacing, white-space.
            Text Indentation: text-indent property is used to specify the indentation of the first line of a text.
            Letter Spacing: specify the space between the characters in a text (letter-spacing: -2px;).
            Line Height: used to specify the space between lines (line-height: 0.8;).
            Word Spacing: specify the space between the words in a text (word-spacing: 10px;).
            White Space: specifies how white-space inside an element is handled (white-space: nowrap;).

            Text Shadow =
            adds shadow to text (text-shadow: 2px 2px;).
            color (text-shadow: 2px 2px red;).
            Text shadow effect (text-shadow: 2px 2px 5px red).

Fonts-
      font-family =
      Generic Font Families--Serif, Sans-serif, Monospace, Cursive, Fantasy, etc.
      All the different font names belong to one of the generic font families. 
      Font Examples
      CSS font-family Property (font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;).

      Font Web Safe =
      are universally installed across all browsers and devices.
      Fallback Fonts-- 
             There is always a chance that a font is not found or is not installed properly
             Example-- there are three font types: Tahoma, Verdana, and sans-serif. The second and third fonts are backups, in case the first one is not found.
                  font-family: Tahoma, Verdana, sans-serif;
       Best Web Safe Fonts for HTML and CSS--Arial (sans-serif),Verdana (sans-serif),Tahoma (sans-serif),Trebuchet MS (sans-serif),Times New Roman (serif),etc.
        
       Font Fallbacks =
       Commonly Used Font Fallbacks (Serif, Sans-serif, Monospace, Cursive, Fantasy) 

       Font Style = 
       font-style-- values: normal, italic, oblique. (font-style: normal;)
       Font Weight--(font-weight: normal;) (font-weight: bold) 
       Font Variant-- lowercase letters are converted to uppercase letters. However, the converted uppercase letters appears in a smaller font size than the original uppercase letters
                        (font-variant: small-caps;) 

       Font Size =
       HTML tags--like <h1> - <h6> for headings and <p>
       (16px=1em) ( 1vw=0.5cm) (1vw = 1%)

        Google Fonts =
        have more than 1000 fonts to choose.
        How To Use Google Fonts, Use Multiple Google Fonts, Styling Google Fonts, Enabling Font Effects.

        Font Pairings =
        Font Pairing Rules.

        Font Shorthand =
        The CSS Font Property--font-style, font-variant, font-weight, font-size/line-height, font-family.
                                (font: italic small-caps bold 12px/30px Georgia, serif;)

Icons-
         How To Add Icons (By using icon library, such as Font Awesome)
         Font Awesome Icons (fontawesome.com)
         Bootstrap Icons--use the Bootstrap glyphicons
         Google Icons

Links-
       Styling Links--(a{color: hotpink;})
       four links states are--a:link(unvisited link), a:visited(user has visited), a:hover(when the user mouses over it), a:active(moment it is clicked).
                                  (a:active {color: blue;})
        Text Decoration-- underline, none. (a:active {text-decoration: underline;})
        Background Color-- (a:hover {background-color: lightgreen;})
        Link Buttons-- combine several CSS properties to display links as boxes/buttons
        More Examples--Mouse over the words to change the cursor style.




          








